cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper deals with the capacity and delay tradeoff in cellular networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication technologies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the use of queueing theory and stochastic geometry models, which are related to information theory and communication theory, respectively. Hence, cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a likely category. The paper also discusses the impact of traffic session payload and primary traffic dynamics, which are related to communication protocols and systems. Therefore, cs.COMM (Computer Communications and Networks) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also possible categories. Finally, the paper mentions the use of cellular networks for delivering secondary communication services, which is related to multimedia systems and applications. Hence, cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category.
